e","England":"Anglie","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Afdød","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Afdød","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Afdød","about 1183":"omkring 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Overleden","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Overleden","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Overleden","about 1183":"circa 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Deceased","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Deceased","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Deceased","about 1183":"about 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Aston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Ad(e)stan</i>, which is usually from Old English <i>Æthelstān</i> (see   Alston  ). It may also be from the much rarer Old English name <i>Ēadstān</i>.","habitational name from any of several places in England called Aston. Most were named with Old English <i>ēast</i> ‘east’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’. In a few cases the first element is <i>æsc</i> ‘ash tree’."],"variants":[{"name":"Alston","meanings":["English and Scottish:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Alstan</i>, which is a coalescence of several different Old English personal names: <i>Æthelstān</i> ‘noble stone’, <i>Ælfstān</i> ‘elf stone’, <i>Ealdstān</i> ‘old stone’, or <i>Ealhstān</i> ‘temple stone’.","habitational name from any of various places called Alston (in Cumbria, Lancashire, Devon, and Somerset) or Alstone (in Gloucestershire and Staffordshire). With the exception of Alston in Cumbria, which is formed with the Old Norse personal name <i>Halfdan</i>, these placenames all consist of an Old English personal name + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’, for example <i>Ælfsige</i> in the case of Alstone in Gloucestershire."]}]},{"name":"Gilbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. This was the name of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilbert de Aston was born in 1154, in Cheshire, England, his father, Richard de Aston, was 23 and his mother, Vanora Van Wempel, was 9. He married Mary Gilbert about 1183, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1199, in Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Surnud","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","about 1183":"umbes 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Kuollut","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Kuollut","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","about 1183":"noin 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, England","England":"England","Aston Juxta Sutton, Chesire England":"Sutton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1154–1199":"1154–1199","–Female":"Décédée","1184–1216":"1184–1216","1199–Male":"1199–Décédé","1132–1195":"1132–1195","1145–Female":"1145–Décédée","about 1183":"environ 1183","1216":"1216","1145":"1145","1199":"1199","1154":"1154","1132":"1132","1184":"1184","1195":"1195","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre","Aston-by-Sutton, Cheshire, England":"Aston by Sutton, Cheshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","Aston Juxta Sut